plot: The gang turns up at the same restaurant for dinner at three different tables. They pretend not to notice they noticed they are noticing each other. Then the one-upmanship begins.

When Mac and Dennis go for their monthly dine at a fancy restaurant known as 'Guigino's', Charlie, Frank, and Dee all seem to be going there too. While they all notice each other, they all try their best to disrupt the other's company by causing a feud, which not only disrupts them, but the whole restaurant.—James Hake
